BINTURONG

Binturong is an animal that most people know and know about their life especially in Kalimantan, Sumatra and Java. Binturong is an animal similar to a weasel but its shape and size is smaller than a weasel. Moreover, binturong has a mustache that grows like a cat.

Binturong has a length of head and body between 60-95 centimeters, with tail length between 50-90 centimeters. Noted, weight binturong about 6-14 kilograms and there are also reached 20 kilograms. This animal is like a cat and a civet who both have feathers that grow almost all of its body, its coat is long and coarse, black, brown slightly reddish or white. At the tip of the ear binturong there are hairs that grow long hair. Feathers contained in the tail is very thick and long, especially at the base so that binturong looks fat.

These carnivora animals often eat ripe fruits and figs, but binturong often also eat leaf buds, young leaves, eggs and small animals such as birds and rodents. So they are classified as omnivorous animals.

The government has already argued that binturong is an animal protected by law because of its increasingly fewer days.
